##D: opposition to democracy, typically, though not always, associated with anti-egalitarianism. [##P: The anti-democracy of right-wing extremism includes an aversion to the democratic rules of the game.]

##D: A branch of economics which focuses on the conditions that exist in and choices constrained by the legal framework of a political constitution. [##P: Similarly, constitutional economics suggests that in matters of constitutional choice it is essential that participants can choose for themselves through the unanimity rule whether the rules are in their own interest.]
##D: (mountaineering) a tool for extracting a nut, chock, etc, from a crack after use.
##D: a machine that cuts raw dough into small portions and rolls each to obtain balls of the same weight and shape.
##D: a triangular cabinet designed to fit in a corner.
##D: a political system in which Cabinet collectively decides the government's direction, especially in regard to legislation passed by the parliament.

##D: the words (as sincerely yours) that conventionally come immediately before the signature of a letter and express the sender's regard for the receiver. [##P: Although a complimentary close is not required, it is almost standard in professional emails. ]

##D: The productiveness of a hen or other egg-laying animal. [##P: Breeders of layers focus on increasing egg yield, weight of eggs, and increasing internal quality such as decreasing the cholesterol content of their production to enhance economic performance.]
##D: a unit of energy equal to the work done by an electron accelerated through a potential difference of one million electron volts.
##D: A thin curtain that allows light into a room but prevents people outside from seeing inside. [##P: My grandma gave me these lovely net curtains, but I'm afraid my room is too modern for them.]

##D: The state or condition of having a flavour or essence of mint. [##P: Paul had come up behind me, and he leaned over to fiddle with the lens, and I could feel him then, his warmth, and I could smell the mintiness of his breath.]
##D: in cartooning, a rounded outline containing words. [##P: Speech bubbles are used not only to include a character's words, but also emotions, voice inflections and unspecified language.]
##D: A stick or pencil made of charcoal, wax, clay, or chalk mixed with coloured pigment; used for drawing or coloring.

##D: device or marking such as postage stamp, printed or stamped impressions, codings, labels, manuscript writings, or any other authorized form of markings affixed or applied to mails to qualify them to be postally serviced. [##W: Prior to the establishment of the UPU in 1874, international mails sometimes bore mixed franking before the world's postal services universally agreed to deliver international mails bearing only the franking of the country of origin.] {##L: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Franking}
##D: a word expressing a number. [##P: Numerals may be attributive, as in two dogs, or pronominal, as in I saw two (of them).]

##D: a lightweight, precast, concrete building material invented in the mid-1920s that simultaneously provides structure, insulation, and fire- and mold-resistance. [##W: Better thermal efficiency of AAC makes it suitable for use in areas with extreme temperature as it eliminates need for separate materials for construction and insulation leading to faster construction and savings.] {##L: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Autoclaved_aerated_concrete}
Lemmas: autoclaved concrete;autoclaved aerated concrete;porous concrete;autoclaved lightweight concrete;autoclaved cellular concrete;AAC

Definition: ##D: an algorithm that implements classification. [##W: Classifier performance depends greatly on the characteristics of the data to be classified.]

##D: measuring how many people are in an audience. [##W: The world's largest audience measurement conference, AM X.0, is presented annually by the Advertising Research Foundation.] {##L: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Audience_measurement}

##D: an electronic device that reduces the dynamic range of an audio signal. [##W: The signal entering a compressor is split, one copy sent to a variable-gain amplifier and the other to a side-chain where a circuit controlled by the signal level applies the required gain to an amplifier stage.]

##D: a type of fortification, like a hornwork, but consisting of a full bastion with the walls on either side ending in half-bastions from which longer flank walls run back towards the main fortress. [##W: The crownwork was used to extend the fortified area in a particular direction often in order to defend a bridge, prevent the enemy occupying an area of high ground, or simply strengthen the overall fortifications in the expected direction of attack.] {##L: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Crownwork}

##D: an organic compound containing two carboxyl functional groups (-COOH). [##W: The most widely used dicarboxylic acid in the industry is adipic acid, which is a precursor used in the production of nylon.] {##L: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dicarboxylic_acid}

##D: the totality of all of the industries involved with the design, manufacture, construction, and maintenance of wind turbines. [##W: The wind power industry is currently undergoing a period of rapid globalization and consolidation, with much of the recent wind farm development occurring outside the older established markets.] {##L: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wind_power_industry}

##D: a film genre concerned with warfare, typically about naval, air, or land battles in the twentieth century, with combat scenes central to the drama. [##W: Nations such as China, Indonesia, Russia and Japan have their own traditions of war film, centred on their own revolutionary wars but taking varied forms, from action and historical drama to wartime romance.] {##L: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/War_film}

##D: a type of ship invented and used by the Vikings for trade, commerce, exploration, and warfare during the Viking Age. [##W: The longships had two methods of propulsion: oars and sail.] {##L: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Longship}

##D: Ammonal is an explosive made up of ammonium nitrate and aluminum powder. [##W: Ammonal used for military mining purposes was generally contained within metal cans or rubberised bags to prevent moisture ingress problems.] {##L: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ammonal}

##D: Blowback is a system of operation for self-loading firearms that obtains energy from the motion of the cartridge case as it is pushed to the rear by expanding gases created by the ignition of the propellant charge. [##W: In most actions that use blowback operation, the breech is not locked mechanically at the time of firing: the inertia of the bolt and recoil spring(s), relative to the weight of the bullet, delays opening of the breech until the bullet has left the barrel] {##L: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Blowback_%28firearms%29}

##D: an element of the trace italienne system of fortification that consists of a pair of demi-bastions. [##W: The hornwork was used to extend the fortified area in a particular direction to prevent the enemy occupying an area of high ground or simply strengthen the overall fortifications in the expected direction of attack.] {##L: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hornwork}

##D: a sowing device that precisely positions seeds in the soil and then covers them. [##W: A seed drill can be pulled across the field using bullocks or a tractor.] {##L: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Seed_drill}

##D: the locative boundary of a certain linguistic feature, such as the pronunciation of a vowel, the meaning of a word, or use of some syntactic feature. [##P: A major isogloss in American English has been identified as the North-Midland isogloss, which demarcates numerous linguistic features, including the Northern Cities vowel shift.] {##L: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Isogloss}

##D: furniture pieces designed to comfortably and aesthetically provide a working surface and house or conceal office equipment including computers, peripherals and cabling for office and home-office users. [##W: The ergonomic desk originated with the beginning of the field of human factors or ergonomics after World War II.] {##L: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Computer_desk}
##D: a synchrotron-based particle accelerator for protons at the Joint Institute for Nuclear Research in Dubna that was operational from 1957 to 2003.

##D: an electronic device that alters how a musical instrument or other audio source sounds. [##W: Guitarists derive their signature sound or "tone" from their choice of instrument, pickups, effects units, and guitar amp.] {##L: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Effects_unit}

##D: a philosophical movement opposing mid-19th century materialism and idealism, developing from Kant's epistemology, considering the thing-in-itself as a borderline concept and emphasizing normative considerations in ethics and jurisprudence. [##P: Fischer was earlier involved in a dispute with the Aristotelian Friedrich Adolf Trendelenburg concerning the interpretation of the results of the Transcendental Aesthetic, a dispute that prompted Hermann Cohen's 1871 seminal work Kants Theorie der Erfahrung, a book often regarded as the foundation of 20th century neo-Kantianism.]

##D: a rig on a sailing vessel that consists of a foresail, such as a jib or genoa sail, that does not reach all the way to the top of the mast. [##W: Fractional rigs were introduced on race boats in order to allow more controllability of the surface of the main sail and also less drag during tacking.] {##L: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fractional_rig}
##D: a chemical compound with the formula H2SeO3. [##W: Selenous acid is analogous to sulfurous acid, but it is more readily isolated.] {##L: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Selenous_acid}

##D: a type of safety glass processed by controlled thermal or chemical treatments to increase its strength compared with normal glass. [##W: As a result of its safety and strength, toughened glass is used in a variety of demanding applications, including passenger vehicle windows, shower doors, architectural glass doors and tables, refrigerator trays, as a component of bulletproof glass, for diving masks, and various types of plates and cookware.] {##L: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Toughened_glass}

##D: A personal information manager (often referred to as a PIM tool or, more simply, a PIM) is a type of application software that functions as a personal organizer. [##W: As an information management tool, a PIM tool's purpose is to facilitate the recording, tracking, and management of certain types of "personal information".] {##L: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Personal_information_manager}

##D: A hydraulic motor is a mechanical actuator that converts hydraulic pressure and flow into torque and angular displacement (rotation). [##W: Conceptually, a hydraulic motor should be interchangeable with a hydraulic pump because it performs the opposite function - similar to the way a DC electric motor is theoretically interchangeable with a DC electrical generator.] {##L: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hydraulic_motor}

##D: 

The arthropod leg is a form of jointed appendage of arthropods, usually used for walking. [##W: Many of the terms used for arthropod leg segments (called podomeres) are of Latin origin, and may be confused with terms for bones: coxa (meaning hip, plural coxae), trochanter (compare trochanter), femur (plural femora), tibia (plural tibiae), tarsus (plural tarsi), ischium (plural ischia), metatarsus, carpus, dactylus (meaning finger), patella (plural patellae).] {##L: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Arthropod_leg}

##D: a space exploration vehicle (rover) designed to move across the surface of the Moon. [##W: Scarab is a new generation lunar rover designed to assist astronauts, take rock and mineral samples, and explore the lunar surface.] {##L: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lunar_rover}

##D: any of a class of organic compounds sharing a common functional group characterized by a nitrogen to nitrogen covalent bond with 4 substituents with at least one of them being an acyl group. [##W: The general structure for a hydrazide is E(=O)-NR-NR2, where the R's are frequently hydrogens.] {##L: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hydrazide}

##D: a word that is treated in pronunciation as forming a part of a neighboring word and that is often unaccented or contracted. [##P: Most languages can adopt theme-rheme structure idiosyncratically — as for English, we often use as for theme constructions — but topic-prominent languages use systematic changes in syntax or even dedicated morpological elements such as the Japanese clitic particle -wa to mark themes and to set them apart from rhemes.]

##D: An induction or asynchronous motor is an AC electric motor in which the electric current in the rotor needed to produce torque is obtained by electromagnetic induction from the magnetic field of the stator winding. [##W: An induction motor therefore does not require mechanical commutation, separate-excitation or self-excitation for all or part of the energy transferred from stator to rotor, as in universal, DC and large synchronous motors.] {##L: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Induction_motor}

##D: a type of small- or medium-sized warship that carried armor in the same way as an armored cruiser: a protective belt and deck. [##W: After 1930, most naval powers concentrated on building light cruisers since they had already built up to the maximum limitations allowed under the Washington treaty.] {##L: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Light_cruiser}

##D: a film that focuses on the lives of criminals. [##W: The stylistic approach to a crime film varies from realistic portrayals of real-life criminal figures, to the far-fetched evil doings of imaginary arch-villains.] {##L: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Crime_film}

##D: Parental leave or family leave is an employee benefit available in almost all countries that provides paid time off work to care for a child or make arrangements for the child's welfare. [##W: The terms "parental leave" and "family leave" include maternity, paternity, and adoption leave.] {##L: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Parental_leave}
##D: an organic compound that is widely used as a flavoring substance. [##W: Anethole is an aromatic, unsaturated ether related to lignols.] {##L: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anethole}
##D: a monosaccharide with seven carbon atoms. {##L: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Heptose}
##D: a tool consisting of a number of fine abrasive slips held in a machine head, rotated and reciprocated to impart a smooth finish to cylinder bores, etc.

##D: An optical lens that darkens on exposure to specific types of light of sufficient intensity, most commonly ultraviolet (UV) radiation. [##W: Typically, photochromic lenses darken substantially in response to UV light in less than one minute, and continue to darken a little more over the next fifteen minutes.] {##L: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Photochromic_lens}

##D: Any of a family of curves defined as the locus of points p, such that each p is on a line that passes through a given fixed point P and intersects a given curve, C, and the distance from p to the point of intersection with C is a specified constant (note that for nontrivial cases two such points p satisfy the criteria, and the resultant curve has two parts). [##P: If you consider a point on a radius of the rolling curve in generating a cardioid that is not on its circumference, the result is a conchoid called the limaçon of Pascal.]

##D: a press in which pressure is exerted by means of a screw. [##P: The screw press was first invented and used by the Romans in the first century AD, primarily in wine and olive oil production.] {##L: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Screw_press}

##D: A small flat pads made of cotton, used for medical or cosmetic purposes. [##P: The easiest way of removing nail polish is to soak a cotton pad in nail polish remover and let it sit on the nail for one minute.] {##L: https://en.wikipedia.org/?title=Cotton_pad}

##D: a mechanical piece of climbing equipment used to control a rope during belaying, designed to improve belay safety for the climber by allowing the belayer to manage their duties with minimal physical effort. [##W: Belay devices usually attach to the harness of the belayer via a carabiner, and are usually made of aluminium or an alloy.] {##L: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Belay_device}

##D: road signs which are used to set the obligations of all traffic which use a specific area of road. [##W: The mandatory sign group is not used in Australia, Ecuador, or the United States, none of which are signatories to the Vienna Convention.] {##L: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mandatory_sign}
Notes: hypernym of pl-470663 to ewn-06806967-n, 'road sign' as new element of this synset

Definition: ##D: The breeding season is the most suitable season, usually with favourable conditions and abundant food and water, for breeding. [##W: The Passenger pigeon is a famous example of probably the most numerous land bird on the American continent which had evolved for communal breeding that went extinct due to large scale hunting in its communal breeding grounds during the breeding season and its inability to breed in smaller numbers.] {##L: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Seasonal_breeder#Breeding_Season}

##D: the common name for the resinous, partially combusted particulate matter produced by the burning of tobacco and other plant material in the act of smoking. [##W: There is a common misconception that the tar in cigarettes is equivalent to the tar used on roads.] {##L: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tar_%28tobacco_residue%29}

##D: The use of electroreception to locate surrounding objects. [##P: Sharks and rays (members of the subclass Elasmobranchii), such as the lemon shark, rely heavily on electrolocation in the final stages of their attacks, as can be demonstrated by the robust feeding response elicited by electric fields similar to those of their prey.]

##D: any of a group of isomers in which atoms are linked in the same order but differ in their spatial arrangement. [##W: A configurational stereoisomer is a stereoisomer of a reference molecule that has the opposite configuration at a stereocenter (e.g., R- vs S- or E- vs Z-).] {##L: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stereoisomerism}

##D: a motion picture whose storyline involves fast-paced activity and conflict, usually including such elements as a heroic protagonist, violent fights, acrobatic stunts, chase scenes, and gunplay. [##P: Reactions to action films containing significant amounts of CGI have been mixed as films that use computer animations to create unrealistic, highly unbelievable events are often met with criticism.] {##L: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Action_film}

##D: a shelter for humans or domesticated animals and livestock based on a hole or depression dug into the ground; can be fully recessed into the earth, with a flat roof covered by ground, semi-recessed, with a constructed wood or sod roof standing out, or dug into a hillside. [##P: Dugouts are one of the most ancient types of human housing known to archeologists, and the same methods have evolved into modern "earth shelter" technology.] {##L: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dugout_(shelter)}

##D: the units of measure to measure the quantity and traffic of transportation used in transportation statistics, planning, and their related fields. {##L: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Units_of_transportation_measurement}

##D: An injector, ejector, steam ejector, steam injector, eductor-jet pump or thermocompressor is a type of pump. [##W: Depending on the specific application, an injector can take the form of an eductor-jet pump, a water eductor, a vacuum ejector, a steam-jet ejector, or an aspirator.] {##L: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Injector}

##D: a market in which people and entities can trade financial securities, commodities, and other fungible items of value at low transaction costs and at prices that reflect supply and demand. [##W: Financial markets attract funds from investors and channel them to corporations—they thus allow corporations to finance their operations and achieve growth.] {##L: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Financial_market}

##D: a logarithmic unit which measures information or entropy, based on base 10 logarithms and powers of 10. [##W: The ban pre-dates Shannon's use of bit as a unit of information by at least eight years, and remains in use in the early 21st Century.] {##L: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ban_(unit)}

##D: a sugar-rich sticky liquid, secreted by aphids and some scale insects as they feed on plant sap. [##W: Honeydew is collected by certain species of birds, wasps, stingless bees and honey bees, which process it into a dark, strong honey (honeydew honey).] {##L: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Honeydew_%28secretion%29}

##D: Drum memory was a magnetic data storage device invented by Gustav Tauschek in 1932 in Austria. [##W: A drum memory contained a large metal cylinder, coated on the outside surface with a ferromagnetic recording material.] {##L: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Drum_memory}

##D: a part of a book, most often found with hardcover bindings, that consists of a small cord or strip of material affixed near the spine to provide structural reinforcement and sometimes decorative effect. [##W: When endbands are used for decorative purposes only they may be glued in place rather than sewn, though at a loss of reinforcing strength.] {##L: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Endband}
##D: a term encompassing a number of religious institutes of the Catholic Church, such as the Order of St. Ursula or the Ursulines of the Roman Union. {##L: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ursulines}
##D:  a compound that contains a SeO32− anion.
##D: One of the speakers on stage pointing towards the performers to help them hear themselves.

##D: the currency of eight independent states in West Africa: Benin, Burkina Faso, Guinea-Bissau, Ivory Coast, Mali, Niger, Sénégal and Togo. [##W: The Central African CFA franc is of equal value to the West African CFA franc, and is in circulation in several central African states.] {##L: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/West_African_CFA_franc}

##D: an anti-inflammatory agent that is produced from willow bark.
[##W: Salicin is an alcoholic β-glucoside.] {##L: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Salicin}

##D: a close combat weapon in which the main fighting part of the weapon is fitted to the end of a long shaft, typically of wood, thereby extending the user's effective range. [##P: Because they contain relatively little metal, polearms are cheap to make, which has made them the favored weapon of peasant levies.] {##L: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pole_weapon}

##D: a word (as anthropology, kilocycle, builder) consisting of any of various combinations of words, combining forms, or affixes. [##P: Also common in English is another type of verb–noun (or noun–verb) compound, in which an argument of the verb is incorporated into the verb, which is then usually turned into a gerund, such as breastfeeding, finger-pointing, etc.]

##D: a heat exchanger which converts steam from its gaseous to its liquid state at a pressure below atmospheric pressure. [##W: In thermal power plants, the purpose of a surface condenser is to condense the exhaust steam from a steam turbine to obtain maximum efficiency, and also to convert the turbine exhaust steam into pure water (referred to as steam condensate) so that it may be reused in the steam generator or boiler as boiler feed water.] {##L: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Surface_condenser}

##D: a meter of poetry consisting of three iambic units per line. [##P: In the dramatic forms of tragedy and comedy, iambic trimeter was used mainly for the verses "spoken" by a character, that is, the dialogue rather than the choral passages.] {##L: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iambic_trimeter}

##D: an electromechanical machine designed to assist in summarizing information and, later, accounting.  [##W: In its basic form, a tabulating machine would read one card at a time, print portions (fields) of the card on fan-fold paper, possibly rearranged, and add one or more numbers punched on the card to one or more counters, called accumulators.] {##L: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tabulating_machine}

##D: a set of electrical and electronic elements used to handle two-way communication (street to home) in houses, apartments or villas. [##P: The door phone is connected to a secure communication system used to control the opening of the door giving access to any kind of buildings, offices, or apartment blocks.] {##L: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Door_phone}

##D: a white or yellowish crystalline heterocyclic compound extracted from coal tar and used in perfumery, medicine, and as a flavouring agent. [##W:  Indole is widely distributed in the natural environment and can be produced by a variety of bacteria. ] {##L: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Indole}

##D: the name of an epoch or era within a four age cycle in Hindu philosophy. [##W:  Like Summer, Spring, Winter and Autumn, each yuga involves stages or gradual changes which the earth and the consciousness of mankind goes through as a whole.] {##L: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yuga}

##D: sports equipment used during rock or any other type of climbing. [##W: A haul bag refers to a large, tough, and often unwieldy bag into which supplies and climbing equipment may be thrown.] {##L: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rock-climbing_equipment}

##D: school of anthropology concerned with long-term culture change and with the similar patterns of development that may be seen in unrelated, widely separated cultures. [##P: Neo-evolutionism was the first in a series of modern multi-lineal evolution theories.]

##D: A software engine refers to a central part of a computer program.  [##W: Examples of software engines include relational database engines, workflow engines, inference engines and search engines.] {##L: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Software_engine}

##D: Either of two letters in Cyrillic alphabets, which originally represented phonemically the ultra-short vowels in Slavic languages. [##P: For determining whether a yer is strong or weak, it is necessary to break the continuous flow of speech into individual words, or prosodic units (phrases which have only a single stressed syllable, and typically include a preposition or other clitic words).]

##D: a sign erected at the side of or above roads to give instructions or provide information to road users. [##W: The earliest road signs were milestones, giving distance or direction; for example, the Romans erected stone columns throughout their empire giving the distance to Rome.] {##L: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Traffic_sign}

##D: The Western concert flute (also called transverse flute, C flute or Boehm flute) is a side-blown woodwind instrument made of metal or wood. [##W: The dimensions and key system of the modern western concert flute and its close relatives are almost completely the work of the great flautist, composer, acoustician and silversmith, Theobald Boehm, who patented his system in 1847.] {##L: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Western_concert_flute#In_jazz_and_rock}
Lemmas: C flute;Boehm flute;transverse flute;Western concert flute

Definition: ##D: An ion-exchange resin or ion-exchange polymer is an insoluble matrix (or support structure) normally in the form of small (0.5-1 mm diameter) beads, usually white or yellowish, fabricated from an organic polymer substrate.  [##W: Sodium polystyrene sulfonate is a strongly acidic ion-exchange resin and is used to treat hyperkalemia.] {##L: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ion-exchange_resin}

##D: a hydrocarbon with a double or  triple covalent bond between adjacent carbon atoms. [##W: Except for aromatic compounds, unsaturated hydrocarbons are highly reactive and undergo addition reactions to their multiple bonds.] {##L: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Unsaturated_hydrocarbon}
##D: a tower with pivoting shutters, also known as blades or paddles, used for conveying information by means of visual signals, read when the shutter is in a fixed position.

##D: a simple type of soup where a basic roux is thinned with cream or milk and then mushrooms and/or mushroom broth are added. [##P: Canned cream of mushroom soup has been described as "America's béchamel".] {##L: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cream_of_mushroom_soup}

##D: the currency of six independent states in central Africa: Cameroon, Central African Republic, Chad, Republic of the Congo, Equatorial Guinea and Gabon. [##W: In several west African states, the West African CFA franc, which is of equal value to the Central African CFA franc, is in circulation.] {##L: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Central_African_CFA_franc}

##D: the cost of participating in a market. [##P: The buyer of a used car faces a variety of different transaction costs: the costs of finding a car and determining the car's condition, the costs of negotiating a price with the seller, and the costs of ensuring that the seller delivers the car in the promised condition.] {##L: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Transaction_cost}
##D:  a mineral ore of zinc. [##W: Smithsonite is a variably colored trigonal mineral which only rarely is found in well formed crystals. ] {##L: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Smithsonite}

##D: a Common Slavonic nasal vowel in the early Cyrillic and Glagolitic alphabets. [##P: The names of the letters do not imply capitalization, as both little and big yus exist in majuscule and minuscule variants.]

##D: a subfield of computer science that explores the study and construction of algorithms that can learn from and make predictions on data. [##W: As a scientific endeavour, machine learning grew out of the quest for artificial intelligence.] {##L: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Machine_learning}

##D: a valve used to control conditions such as flow, pressure, temperature, and liquid level by fully or partially opening or closing in response to signals received from controllers. [##W: The opening or closing of control valves is usually done automatically by electrical, hydraulic or pneumatic actuators.] {##L: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Control_valves}

##D: The quality of being an animal that eats meat as the main part of its diet. [##PP: "The too obvious fact that a large portion of animals are carnivorous neither proves nor justifies the carnivorousness of the human species."]

##D: an electronic device that increases the dynamic range of the audio signal. [##W: Expanders are generally used to make quiet sounds even quieter by reducing the level of an audio signal that falls below a set threshold level.]

##D: an electro-mechanical device that converts the angular position or motion of a shaft or axle to an analog or digital code. [##W: Rotary encoders are used in many applications that require precise shaft unlimited rotation—including industrial controls, robotics, special purpose photographic lenses, computer input devices (such as optomechanical mice and trackballs), controlled stress rheometers, and rotating radar platforms.] {##L: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rotary_encoder}

##D: a relative magnitude of two selected numerical values taken from an enterprise's financial statements. [##P: Financial ratios can be expressed as a decimal value, such as 0.10, or given as an equivalent percent value, such as 10%.] {##L: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Financial_ratio}

##D: a toy which imitates real weapons, but is designed for children to play with. [##W: Many newer toy weapons are brightly colored and oddly shaped to appeal to children and distinguish them from the real thing.] {##L: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Toy_weapon}

##D: a genre of film in which the main emphasis is on humor. [##W: Most British comedy films of the early 1970s were spin-offs of television series, including Dad's Army and On the Buses.] {##L: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Comedy_film}

##D: A version of the law of large numbers that states that the sample average converges almost surely to the expected value. [##P: The mathematical relation between these two experiments was recognized in 1909 by the French mathematician Émile Borel, who used the then new ideas of measure theory to give a precise mathematical model and to formulate what is now called the strong law of large numbers for fair coin tossing.]

##D: a chemical compound with chemical formula BN, consisting of equal numbers of boron and nitrogen atoms. [##W: Boron nitride has potential use in nanotechnology.] {##L: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Boron_nitride}

##D: a stately dance of the Shinto religion that now forms a part of Japanese village festivals. [##P: Kagura, in particular those forms that involve storytelling or reenactment of fables, is also one of the primary influences on the Noh theatre.]

##D: in Western painting, movement in France that represented both an extension of Impressionism and a rejection of that style’s inherent limitations. [##P: The real influence of Paris across the Atlantic came not with Impressionism but with the post-impressionism of Toulouse Lautrec and Cézanne, the Modernism of Picasso and Matisse and the radical experiments of the Surrealists.]
##D: A data storage device is any device for recording (storing) information (data). [##W: Many data storage devices are also media players.] {##L: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Data_storage_device}

##D: a cyclic intramolecular ester derived from a hydroxy acid. [##W: Lactones are formed by intramolecular esterification of the corresponding hydroxycarboxylic acids, which takes place spontaneously when the ring that is formed is five- or six-membered.] {##L: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lactone}

##D: an apparatus used for filtration consisting of a set of frames covered with filter cloth on both sides, between which the liquid to be filtered is pumped. [##W: The filter press is used in fixed-volume and batch operations, which means that the operation must be stopped to discharge the filter cake before the next batch can be started.] {##L: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Filter_press}

##D: A kitchen appliance for deep frying; its size depends on intended use. [##W: Deep fryers are used for cooking many fast foods, and making them crisp.] {##L: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Deep_fryer}

##D: a substance which contains living microorganisms which, when applied to seed, plant surfaces, or soil, colonizes the rhizosphere or the interior of the plant and promotes growth by increasing the supply or availability of primary nutrients to the host plant. [##W: Bio-fertilizers add nutrients through the natural processes of nitrogen fixation, solubilizing phosphorus, and stimulating plant growth through the synthesis of growth-promoting substances.] {##L: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Biofertilizer}

##D: a motor vehicle designed to carry liquefied loads, dry bulk cargo or gases on roads. [##W: Some less visible distinctions amongst tank trucks have to do with their intended use: compliance with human food regulations, refrigeration capability, acid resistance, pressurization capability, and more.] {##L: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tank_truck}

##D: (linguistics) the grammatical and lexical linking within a text or sentence that holds a text together and gives it meaning. [##P: While lexical cohesion is obviously achieved by the selection of vocabulary, the other types of cohesion are considered as grammatical cohesion.]

##D: A genre of electronic dance music with a fast tempo, repetitive phrasing, and often a hypnotic effect. [##P: Classic trance employs a 4/4 time signature, a tempo of 125 to 150 BPM, and 32 beat phrases and is somewhat faster than house music]

##D: #DD: The name 'ecdysteroid' refers to the  insect moulting and sex hormones which include ecdysone and its homologues such as 20-hydroxyecdysone. [##W: Ecdysteroids also occur in other invertebrates where they can play a different role.] {##L: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ecdysteroid}
##D: A microphone that works via electromagnetic induction. {##L: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Microphone#Dynamic_microphone}

##D: A systematic approach to determining the optimum use of scarce resources, involving comparison of two or more alternatives in achieving a specific objective under the given assumptions and constraints. [##P: After the economic analysis was over, we would have a better idea of how to use the resources that were scarce.]

##D: a type of sword or dagger typical of the Germanic peoples of the Migration period and the Early Middle Ages, especially the Saxons. [##P: Initially, seaxes were found in combination with double-edged swords and were probably intended as side arm.] {##L: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Seax}

##D: The practice of eating mainly vegetarian food, but making occasional exceptions for social, pragmatic, cultural, or nutritional reasons. [##P: Flexitarianism will be the next ‘mega trend’ leading to sales of vegetarian foods in the UK to grow by 10% by 2016, according to food trends agency The Food People.]

##D: a light wooden ard, consisting of two body ards, with their parallel beams forming the two shafts for a single horse-drawn tillage implement with two socket shares. [##W: The sokha adapts the body ard to a single-animal harness following the pattern of a shaft-drawn cart and adds a spade-like component that turned over the soil.] {##L: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sokha}

##D: the totality of all of the industries involved in the production and sale of energy, including fuel extraction, manufacturing, refining and distribution. [##W: Some parts of the energy industry generate considerable pollution, including toxic and greenhouse gases from fuel combustion, nuclear waste from the generation of nuclear power, and oil spillages as a result of petroleum extraction.] {##L: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Energy_industry}

##D: a form of music consisting of sounds produced by oscillating electric currents either controlled from an instrument panel or keyboard or prerecorded on magnetic tape. [##P: In Cologne, what would become the most famous electronic music studio in the world was officially opened at the radio studios of the NWDR in 1953, though it had been in the planning stages as early as 1950 and early compositions were made and broadcast in 1951.]

##D: A collar that resembles the polo neck with the soft fold at its top and the way it stands up around the neck, but both ends of the tube forming the collar are sewn to the neckline. [##W: The mock polo neck clings to the neck smoothly, is easy to manufacture, and works well with a zip closure.]  {##L: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Polo_neck}
Lemmas: mock turtleneck collar;mock polo neck collar

Definition: ##D: any of a group of isomeric hydrocarbons that are classified as terpenes. [##P: α-Terpinene is an example of a terpinene.] {##L: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Terpinene}

##D: a milling machine with automatic tool changers, tool magazines or carousels, CNC control, coolant systems, and enclosures. [##P: After the advent of computer numerical control (CNC), milling machines evolved into machining centers, generally classified as vertical machining centers (VMCs) and horizontal machining centers (HMCs).] {##L: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Milling_(machining)}

##D: A cock ring is a ring that can be placed around a penis, usually at the base, primarily to slow the flow of blood from the erect penile tissue, thus maintaining an erection for a much longer period of time. [##W: Cock rings can be worn around just the penis or both the penis and scrotum, or just the scrotum alone, though this is usually called a testicle cuff.] {##L: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cock_ring}

##D: a historical type of personal armor made from iron or steel plates, which superseded mail during the 14th century. [##W: The increasing power and availability of firearms and the nature of large, state-supported infantry led to more portions of plate armour being cast off in favour of cheaper, more mobile troops.] {##L: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Plate_armour}

##D: A DC motor is any of a class of electrical machines that converts direct current electrical power into mechanical power. [##W: Nearly all types of DC motors have some internal mechanism, either electromechanical or electronic, to periodically change the direction of current flow in part of the motor.] {##L: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DC_motor}

##D:  an orthorhombic gold telluride mineral which can contain a relatively small amount of silver in the structure. [##W: Both of the chemically similar gold-silver tellurides, calaverite and sylvanite, are in the monoclinic crystal system, whereas krennerite is orthorhombic.] {##L: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Krennerite}

##D: alkene hydrocarbon which contains a closed ring of carbon atoms, but has no aromatic character. [##W: Due to geometrical considerations, smaller cycloalkenes are almost always the cis isomers, and the term cis tends to be omitted from the names.] {##L: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cycloalkene}

##D: any simple probabilistic classifier based on applying Bayes' theorem with strong (naive) independence assumptions between the features. [##W: Naive Bayes classifiers are highly scalable, requiring a number of parameters linear in the number of variables (features/predictors) in a learning problem.] {##L: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Naive_Bayes_classifier}

##D: A sex toy is an object or device that is primarily used to facilitate human sexual pleasure, such as a dildo or vibrator.  [##W: Many popular sex toys are designed to resemble human genitals and may be vibrating or non-vibrating.] {##L: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sex_toy}

##D: a fortification composed of many projecting triangular bastions (usually from five to eight), specifically designed to cover each other; first seen in the mid-15th century in Italy. [##W: Star forts were employed by Michelangelo in the defensive earthworks of Florence, and refined in the sixteenth century by Baldassare Peruzzi and Scamozzi.] {##L: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Star_fort}
Lemmas: trace italienne;star-shaped fortress;star fort;bastion fort;star fortress

Definition: ##D:  an antipsychotic medication used in the treatment of schizophrenia. [##W: Sertindole is not approved for use in the United States.] {##L: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sertindole}

##D: a substituted tryptamine alkaloid and a serotonergic psychedelic substance, present in most psychedelic mushrooms together with its phosphorylated counterpart psilocybin. [##W: The mind-altering effects of psilocin are highly variable and subjective and resemble those of LSD and DMT.] {##L: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Psilocin}

##D: a weapon used in hand-to-hand combat such as a bladed weapon or a blunt weapon. [##P: There are two basic divisions of melee weapons: edged weapons, of which examples include swords, spears, axes, knives, and shovels; and blunt weapons, such as clubs, hammers, staffs, maces, and flails.] {##L: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Melee_weapon}

##D: Microsoft Entourage was an e-mail client and personal information manager developed by Microsoft for Mac OS 8.5 and higher. [##W: Entourage provided email, calendar, address book, task list, note list, and project manager functionality.] {##L: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Microsoft_Entourage}

##D: the name of two currencies used in Africa which are guaranteed by the French treasury. [##W: The value of the CFA franc has been widely criticized as being too high, which many economists believe favours the urban elite of the African countries, which can buy imported manufactured goods cheaply at the expense of farmers who cannot easily export agricultural products.] {##L: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/CFA_franc}

##D: Microsoft Outlook is a personal information manager from Microsoft, available as a part of the Microsoft Office suite. [##W: Microsoft Outlook has replaced Microsoft's previous scheduling and mail program, Schedule+ and Exchange Client.] {##L: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Microsoft_Outlook}

##D: Kontact is a personal information manager and groupware software suite developed by KDE; it supports calendars, contacts, notes, to-do lists, news, and email. [##W: Technically speaking, Kontact only refers to a small umbrella application that unifies different stand-alone applications under one user interface.] {##L: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kontact}

##D: a simple light plough without a mouldboard. [##W: Rather than cutting and turning the soil to produce ridged furrows, the ard breaks up a narrow strip of soil and cuts a shallow furrow (or drill), leaving intervening strips undisturbed.] {##L: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ard_(plough)}

##D: In firearms terminology, the mechanism that handles the ammunition (loads, locks, fires, and extracts the cartridges). [##W: Actions can be categorized in several ways, including single action versus double action, break action versus bolt action, and others.] {##L: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Action_%28firearms%29}

##D: a classifier that constructs a hyperplane or set of hyperplanes in a high- or infinite-dimensional space, which can be used for classification, regression, or other tasks. [##W: The SVM algorithm has been widely applied in the biological and other sciences.] {##L: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Support_vector_machine}

##D: one of a group of toxins from the death cap (Amanita phalloides) known as phallotoxins. [##W: Phalloidin was one of the first cyclic peptides to be discovered.] {##L: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Phalloidin}
